James McWilliams Blue Line, Libelant-Appellee, v. Steam Tug MARY TRACY, Her Engines, etc.; Thomas Tracy, Claimant-Appellant; Standard Oil Company of New York, Respondent-Appellee. M. K. Neville, Libelant-Appellee, v. SAME. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 17, 1926.) Nos. 337, 338. James A. Martin, of New York City, for appellant. Courtland Palmer, of New York City, for appellee Standard Oil Co. Paul Speer, of New York City, for appellee Neville.

Before HOUGH, MANTON, and HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decrees affirmed, with costs,
